sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K887003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part contain four enzymes. Each of the former three enzymes(alsS, ilvC& ilvD) linked with a zinc finger. The three enzymes could convert pyruvate into 2-ketoisoalerate(the Intermediate of isobutanol). The final enzyme(kivD)could change 2-ketoisoalerate into isobutyraldehyde, which would be converted into isobutanol by ADH in E.coli. This is a complete circuit to produce isobutanol.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: WU, CHENG-HSUAN
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The circuit is optimized from 2011 NCTU_FORMOSA.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We add zinc fingers in front of enzymes in the circuit, and therefore the enzymes could bind the DNA program in order. It help enhance the efficiency of isobutanol production .

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K539713
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the coding region of AlsS from Bacillus subtilis. It encodes alpha-acetolactate synthase protein which is part of isobutanol biosynthesis pathway.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yang, Yi-Pei
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Because of the four RE site, EcoR1, Xba1, Spe1 and Pst1, before and after the coding sequence, those RE site should not exist in coding sequence. There are two Pst1 site, one Xba1 site and one EcoR1 site in original sequence of AlsS. However, those RE site in AlsS has been modified by point mutation.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K539711
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the coding region of ilvC from Escherichia coli str. K-12 substr(MG1655). It encodes ketol-acid reductoisomerase NAD(P)-binding which is part of the isobutanol biosynthesis pathway.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yang, Yi-Pei
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It comes from Escherichia coli str. K-12 substr. MG1655
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Because of the four RE site, EcoR1, Xba1, Spe1 and Pst1, before and after the coding gene, we have to delete those RE site in kivd. The RE site in the part has been modified by point mutation.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: p(tetR)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Sequence for pTet inverting regulator driven by the TetR protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: June Rhee, Connie Tao, Ty Thomson, Louis Waldman
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Lutz, R., Bujard, H., Nucleic Acids Research (1997) 25, 1203-1210.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: BBa_R0040 TetR-Regulated Promoter is based on a cI promoter. It has been modified to include two TetR binding sites and the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K539714
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: kivd is the coding sequence from Lactococcus lactis subsp. It encodes alpha-ketoisovalerate decarboxylase which is responsible for the decarboxylation into aldehydes of α-keto acids derived from amino acid transamination. This is part of the isobutanol biosynthesis pathway.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yang, Yi-Pei
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It is cloned form Lactococcus lactis subsp. lactis KF147
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: In order to design the four RE site, EcoR1, Xba1, Spe1 and Pst1, before and after the coding region.However, there is one RE site, EcoR1, in kivd. The RE site in kivd has been modified by point mutation.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
